/a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Summoned Armor and muzzle</span><hr size=1> Do giving the pet these items actually help at all?  Granted I didnt do any formal testing, but while soloing in seb today i forgot to hand my pet the armor i summoned for him and the muzzle and on a dar knight he went down to 51percent,   then i gave him the armor and muzzle, on another dar knight, with me doing the same amount of damage, he dropped to 31percent health.  Im just wondering if there have been tests to prove that these items do in fact help the pet live longer/ do more dmg. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=stehle>stehle</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 27<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 6:18 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=841.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned Armor and muzzle</span><hr size=1> Without a doubt these help.  I've been giving armor to my pets ever since I received the first Summon Leather armor spell.  Huge difference in damage mitigation.  Now that I can summon plate it makes even more difference.  Case in point, using a 44 focused water pet I can handle 2 HGs in RM at the most.  With the pet armored, I can take on 3 HGs.  I'm sure that there are parses somewhere-- check in the Epic Pet section.<br>
<br>
Casala <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fashionmagician>FashionMagician</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 13<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 6:48 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=841.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned Armor and muzzle</span><hr size=1> Make sure you take each piece of summoned armor out of the bag and give them to pet.  Summoning the bag of armor and then just handing the bag to the pet does nothing (which had been my mistake previously).<br>
<br>
 <p><B>Zress</B> <BR>
<B>Fashion Magician</B> <BR> <I> <B>"((POOF!)) Your in style!"</I> </B></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=naladini>naladini</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 601<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 7:01 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=841.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Summoned Armor and muzzle</span><hr size=1> Keep in mind that most of the parsing of BO + Muzzle was done by level 60 players.<br>
<br>
VI/SOE mentioned that pet haste caps scale with the level of the caster. It would be my hope that both of these spells are immediately useful/stackable at level 56, but I haven't seen any evidence to prove it one way or another.<br>
<br>
I believe I had read that Ancient BO Blaze + Muzzle was somewhat pointless at level 60 due to the cap, but I'm curious as to how well the cap rises after level 60.<br>
<br>
As for armor, it does make a difference, but as you get higher in level, it makes far less of a difference than it did when you would have first gotten the spell, due to the increased ATK rating of the mobs you are now fighting. <p><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=381929"> Naladini </a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
<br>
Conjurer of the 55th Season-Stormhammer<br>
<br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=camelebrodcet>CamelebRodcet</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 3<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 7:12 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=841.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Armor </span><hr size=1> I duo quite a bit with a cleric friend and he says that he can tell when healing pet a noticable diffrence.   Its not a major change but it is noticable. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=dabrighter2>Dabrighter2</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 6<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 7:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=841.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Armor </span><hr size=1> Another thing to keep in mind is that Armour {summoned armor} and Hit Points {summoned focus items, pets don't use the effects} is much more effective on the High agility Pets {Air, Water} than the Low agility pets.    <br>
<br>
For me at 40th Level fighting dark blues solo, the Earth Pet's agility is so low that it is often hit for max on every blow.  Adding the AC makes the occasionally not hit for max and the Hit Points means it it worth maybe one or two more hits.   <br>
<br>
However, adding the AC to the Air pet means it is hit for Max much less often and most blows are mitigated for a larger amount.  The hit points added from the focus effects are worth maybe 3 times as much because of the added mitigation of the Air pets AC.  This makes the heals much more effective on the Air pet as well.  <br>
<br>
At this level, I give my Water and Air pet as much armor/Focus items as I can to mitigated the damage as much as possible.  The Earth pet I just burnout and use pet chaining.  The fire I only tend to use in groups and just summon and use burnout on it.  <br>
  <br>
I have a 15th level ranger on a second account that I cast Feet like cat, {a 10 point agility buff} on my pet.  I can never tell when cast on the earth pet.  Sometimes I notice it on my water pet.  I always notice it on my air pet.  <br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=ciggon>Ciggon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#333333>(11/26/02 7:59 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=841.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Armor </span><hr size=1> Using the 57 earth pet, I honestly see no difference with / without him using armor.  I'll put it on him if I have kei and am waiting on spawns; but if not, I don't bother because the effect is either not there, or it is so random that its not worth the bother of trying to keep the pet alive.  It could just be the earth pet; the 57 earth seems to be no better at tanking than the 53 air; except that it does more damage.  I'm typically soloing in PoJ, so that may also have something to do with why the armor seems to not have much effect.  From what I've found, its much more efficient to keep the pet's total mana cost at a level where you can just resummon after a few fights when its near dead. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showPrevMessage?topicID=841.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showNextMessage?topicID=841.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm29.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=841.topic&index=6><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/softsky/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfr